      "review_summary": "The branch adds a Telegram rich-link href allow-list, suppresses local and relative Markdown href anchors to visible label text, and adds formatter plus mocked send-path regression tests.\n\nPR surface: Source +12, Tests +59. Total +71 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible. Current main and v2026.6.8 still render explicit local or relative Markdown hrefs as Telegram rich `<a href>` anchors, and the linked issue includes live `RICH_MESSAGE_URL_INVALID` logs from shipped installs.",
